-- GE offer for Alstom has improved, French official says
-- By Julien Ponthus
-- Wed May 28, 2014 03:58AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, May 28 (Reuters) - U.S. conglomerate General Electric's <GE.N> offer for French train and turbines maker Alstom <ALSO.PA> has been improved, notably concerning the impact on jobs, an official at French President Francois Hollande's office said on Wednesday.

On Tuesday evening, GE Chief Executive Jeff Immelt told French lawmakers his group would make detailed commitments to increase jobs in France, including by opening new sites.